{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":921,"text":"This is my great uncle,"},{"time":2918,"text":"my father's father's younger brother."},{"time":5936,"text":"His name was Joe McKenna."},{"time":8142,"text":"He was a young husband\nand a semi-pro basketball player"},{"time":13089,"text":"and a fireman in New York City."},{"time":17407,"text":"Family history says\nhe loved being a fireman,"},{"time":20007,"text":"and so in 1938, on one of his days off,"},{"time":23542,"text":"he elected to hang out at the firehouse."},{"time":27019,"text":"To make himself useful that day,\nhe started polishing all the brass,"},{"time":31218,"text":"the railings on the fire truck,\nthe fittings on the walls,"},{"time":34612,"text":"and one of the fire hose nozzles,"},{"time":36957,"text":"a giant, heavy piece of metal,"},{"time":39465,"text":"toppled off a shelf and hit him."},{"time":43574,"text":"A few days later,\nhis shoulder started to hurt."},{"time":47382,"text":"Two days after that, he spiked a fever."},{"time":50656,"text":"The fever climbed and climbed."},{"time":53141,"text":"His wife was taking care of him,"},{"time":55091,"text":"but nothing she did made a difference,\nand when they got the local doctor in,"},{"time":59393,"text":"nothing he did mattered either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62149,"text":"They flagged down a cab\nand took him to the hospital."},{"time":65911,"text":"The nurses there recognized right away\nthat he had an infection,"},{"time":69905,"text":"what at the time they would\nhave called \"blood poisoning,\""},{"time":74061,"text":"and though they probably didn't say it,"},{"time":76174,"text":"they would have known right away"},{"time":78031,"text":"that there was nothing they could do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81770,"text":"There was nothing they could do\nbecause the things we use now"},{"time":84788,"text":"to cure infections didn't exist yet."},{"time":87737,"text":"The first test of penicillin,\nthe first antibiotic,"},{"time":91173,"text":"was three years in the future."},{"time":93843,"text":"People who got infections\neither recovered, if they were lucky,"},{"time":98547,"text":"or they died."},{"time":100322,"text":"My great uncle was not lucky."},{"time":102411,"text":"He was in the hospital for a week,\nshaking with chills,"},{"time":105708,"text":"dehydrated and delirious,"},{"time":107566,"text":"sinking into a coma as his organs failed."},{"time":110468,"text":"His condition grew so desperate"},{"time":112604,"text":"that the people from his firehouse\nlined up to give him transfusions"},{"time":117234,"text":"hoping to dilute the infection\nsurging through his blood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121497,"text":"Nothing worked. He died."},{"time":125143,"text":"He was 30 years old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128115,"text":"If you look back through history,"},{"time":130088,"text":"most people died the way\nmy great uncle died."},{"time":133362,"text":"Most people didn't die\nof cancer or heart disease,"},{"time":136032,"text":"the lifestyle diseases that afflict us\nin the West today."},{"time":140490,"text":"They didn't die of those diseases\nbecause they didn't live long enough"},{"time":144229,"text":"to develop them."},{"time":146225,"text":"They died of injuries --"},{"time":148338,"text":"being gored by an ox,"},{"time":150823,"text":"shot on a battlefield,"},{"time":152727,"text":"crushed in one of the new factories\nof the Industrial Revolution --"},{"time":156465,"text":"and most of the time from infection,"},{"time":159846,"text":"which finished what those injuries began."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164492,"text":"All of that changed\nwhen antibiotics arrived."},{"time":168599,"text":"Suddenly, infections that had\nbeen a death sentence"},{"time":172198,"text":"became something\nyou recovered from in days."},{"time":175588,"text":"It seemed like a miracle,"},{"time":178630,"text":"and ever since, we have been living inside\nthe golden epoch of the miracle drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185294,"text":"And now, we are coming to an end of it."},{"time":189241,"text":"My great uncle died in the last days\nof the pre-antibiotic era."},{"time":194303,"text":"We stand today on the threshold\nof the post-antibiotic era,"},{"time":199457,"text":"in the earliest days of a time\nwhen simple infections"},{"time":203219,"text":"such as the one Joe had\nwill kill people once again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208884,"text":"In fact, they already are."},{"time":212785,"text":"People are dying of infections again\nbecause of a phenomenon"},{"time":215618,"text":"called antibiotic resistance."},{"time":218381,"text":"Briefly, it works like this."},{"time":220119,"text":"Bacteria compete against each other\nfor resources, for food,"},{"time":225091,"text":"by manufacturing lethal compounds\nthat they direct against each other."},{"time":229758,"text":"Other bacteria, to protect themselves,"},{"time":232103,"text":"evolve defenses against\nthat chemical attack."},{"time":235354,"text":"When we first made antibiotics,"},{"time":237676,"text":"we took those compounds into the lab\nand made our own versions of them,"},{"time":241878,"text":"and bacteria responded to our attack\nthe way they always had."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247674,"text":"Here is what happened next:"},{"time":250098,"text":"Penicillin was distributed in 1943,"},{"time":253488,"text":"and widespread penicillin resistance\narrived by 1945."},{"time":258619,"text":"Vancomycin arrived in 1972,"},{"time":261568,"text":"vancomycin resistance in 1988."},{"time":265028,"text":"Imipenem in 1985,"},{"time":267150,"text":"and resistance to in 1998."},{"time":270192,"text":"Daptomycin, one of\nthe most recent drugs, in 2003,"},{"time":273860,"text":"and resistance to it\njust a year later in 2004."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278575,"text":"For 70 years, we played\na game of leapfrog --"},{"time":282335,"text":"our drug and their resistance,"},{"time":285261,"text":"and then another drug,\nand then resistance again --"},{"time":288906,"text":"and now the game is ending."},{"time":291437,"text":"Bacteria develop resistance so quickly\nthat pharmaceutical companies"},{"time":295477,"text":"have decided making antibiotics\nis not in their best interest,"},{"time":299842,"text":"so there are infections\nmoving across the world"},{"time":302652,"text":"for which, out of the more\nthan 100 antibiotics"},{"time":306111,"text":"available on the market,"},{"time":308340,"text":"two drugs might work with side effects,"},{"time":311754,"text":"or one drug,"},{"time":314238,"text":"or none."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316096,"text":"This is what that looks like."},{"time":318278,"text":"In 2000, the Centers for Disease\nControl and Prevention, the CDC,"},{"time":322458,"text":"identified a single case"},{"time":324501,"text":"in a hospital in North Carolina"},{"time":326753,"text":"of an infection resistant\nto all but two drugs."},{"time":330886,"text":"Today, that infection, known as KPC,"},{"time":335205,"text":"has spread to every state but three,"},{"time":337805,"text":"and to South America, Europe"},{"time":340150,"text":"and the Middle East."},{"time":342867,"text":"In 2008, doctors in Sweden"},{"time":345189,"text":"diagnosed a man from India\nwith a different infection"},{"time":347975,"text":"resistant to all but one drug that time."},{"time":351690,"text":"The gene that creates that resistance,"},{"time":353919,"text":"known as NDM, has now spread\nfrom India into China, Asia, Africa,"},{"time":360444,"text":"Europe and Canada, and the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365129,"text":"It would be natural to hope"},{"time":367688,"text":"that these infections\nare extraordinary cases,"},{"time":371287,"text":"but in fact,"},{"time":373145,"text":"in the United States and Europe,"},{"time":375606,"text":"50,000 people a year"},{"time":378322,"text":"die of infections which no drugs can help."},{"time":382966,"text":"A project chartered\nby the British government"},{"time":386008,"text":"known as the Review\non Antimicrobial Resistance"},{"time":389746,"text":"estimates that the worldwide toll\nright now is 700,000 deaths a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398291,"text":"That is a lot of deaths,"},{"time":402655,"text":"and yet, the chances are good\nthat you don't feel at risk,"},{"time":405767,"text":"that you imagine these people\nwere hospital patients"},{"time":408995,"text":"in intensive care units"},{"time":410713,"text":"or nursing home residents\nnear the ends of their lives,"},{"time":414660,"text":"people whose infections\nare remote from us,"},{"time":417841,"text":"in situations we can't identify with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422455,"text":"What you didn't think about,\nnone of us do,"},{"time":425852,"text":"is that antibiotics support\nalmost all of modern life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431721,"text":"If we lost antibiotics,"},{"time":433932,"text":"here's what else we'd lose:"},{"time":435836,"text":"First, any protection for people\nwith weakened immune systems --"},{"time":440015,"text":"cancer patients, AIDS patients,"},{"time":443475,"text":"transplant recipients, premature babies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447979,"text":"Next, any treatment that installs\nforeign objects in the body:"},{"time":452391,"text":"stents for stroke, pumps for diabetes,"},{"time":456269,"text":"dialysis, joint replacements."},{"time":460193,"text":"How many athletic baby boomers\nneed new hips and knees?"},{"time":463908,"text":"A recent study estimates\nthat without antibiotics,"},{"time":466717,"text":"one out of ever six would die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470664,"text":"Next, we'd probably lose surgery."},{"time":473869,"text":"Many operations are preceded"},{"time":476191,"text":"by prophylactic doses of antibiotics."},{"time":479139,"text":"Without that protection,"},{"time":480811,"text":"we'd lose the ability to open\nthe hidden spaces of the body."},{"time":485015,"text":"So no heart operations,"},{"time":487848,"text":"no prostate biopsies,"},{"time":490680,"text":"no Cesarean sections."},{"time":493792,"text":"We'd have to learn to fear infections\nthat now seem minor."},{"time":498784,"text":"Strep throat used to cause heart failure."},{"time":502592,"text":"Skin infections led to amputations."},{"time":505819,"text":"Giving birth killed,\nin the cleanest hospitals,"},{"time":508722,"text":"almost one woman out of every 100."},{"time":511717,"text":"Pneumonia took three children\nout of every 10."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517220,"text":"More than anything else,"},{"time":519333,"text":"we'd lose the confident way\nwe live our everyday lives."},{"time":524836,"text":"If you knew that any injury\ncould kill you,"},{"time":529043,"text":"would you ride a motorcycle,"},{"time":532289,"text":"bomb down a ski slope,"},{"time":535500,"text":"climb a ladder to hang\nyour Christmas lights,"},{"time":538976,"text":"let your kid slide into home plate?"},{"time":543573,"text":"After all, the first person\nto receive penicillin,"},{"time":546638,"text":"a British policeman named\nAlbert Alexander,"},{"time":550516,"text":"who was so ravaged by infection\nthat his scalp oozed pus"},{"time":554858,"text":"and doctors had to take out an eye,"},{"time":557783,"text":"was infected by doing\nsomething very simple."},{"time":562172,"text":"He walked into his garden\nand scratched his face on a thorn."},{"time":568831,"text":"That British project I mentioned\nwhich estimates that the worldwide toll"},{"time":572481,"text":"right now is 700,000 deaths a year"},{"time":576358,"text":"also predicts that if we can't\nget this under control by 2050,"},{"time":582535,"text":"not long, the worldwide toll\nwill be 10 million deaths a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590127,"text":"How did we get to this point"},{"time":592829,"text":"where what we have to look forward to"},{"time":594864,"text":"is those terrifying numbers?"},{"time":598347,"text":"The difficult answer is,\nwe did it to ourselves."},{"time":602875,"text":"Resistance is an inevitable\nbiological process,"},{"time":605847,"text":"but we bear the responsibility\nfor accelerating it."},{"time":610490,"text":"We did this by squandering antibiotics"},{"time":614043,"text":"with a heedlessness\nthat now seems shocking."},{"time":619408,"text":"Penicillin was sold\nover the counter until the 1950s."},{"time":623494,"text":"In much of the developing world,\nmost antibiotics still are."},{"time":627209,"text":"In the United States, 50 percent"},{"time":630971,"text":"of the antibiotics given\nin hospitals are unnecessary."},{"time":634663,"text":"Forty-five percent of the prescriptions\nwritten in doctor's offices"},{"time":639037,"text":"are for conditions\nthat antibiotics cannot help."},{"time":644577,"text":"And that's just in healthcare."},{"time":647247,"text":"On much of the planet, most meat animals\nget antibiotics every day of their lives,"},{"time":652100,"text":"not to cure illnesses,"},{"time":654376,"text":"but to fatten them up\nand to protect them against"},{"time":657835,"text":"the factory farm conditions\nthey are raised in."},{"time":661806,"text":"In the United States, possibly 80 percent"},{"time":664824,"text":"of the antibiotics sold every year\ngo to farm animals, not to humans,"},{"time":671527,"text":"creating resistant bacteria\nthat move off the farm"},{"time":675203,"text":"in water, in dust,"},{"time":677827,"text":"in the meat the animals become."},{"time":680985,"text":"Aquaculture depends on antibiotics too,"},{"time":683910,"text":"particularly in Asia,"},{"time":685559,"text":"and fruit growing relies on antibiotics"},{"time":688902,"text":"to protect apples, pears,\ncitrus, against disease."},{"time":694491,"text":"And because bacteria can pass\ntheir DNA to each other"},{"time":700117,"text":"like a traveler handing off\na suitcase at an airport,"},{"time":704552,"text":"once we have encouraged\nthat resistance into existence,"},{"time":709360,"text":"there is no knowing where it will spread."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713723,"text":"This was predictable."},{"time":715674,"text":"In fact, it was predicted"},{"time":718506,"text":"by Alexander Fleming,\nthe man who discovered penicillin."},{"time":722941,"text":"He was given the Nobel Prize\nin 1945 in recognition,"},{"time":726935,"text":"and in an interview shortly after,\nthis is what he said:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":731282,"text":"\"The thoughtless person playing\nwith penicillin treatment"},{"time":735549,"text":"is morally responsible\nfor the death of a man"},{"time":738823,"text":"who succumbs to infection"},{"time":741147,"text":"with a pencillin-resistant organism.\""},{"time":744050,"text":"He added, \"I hope this evil\ncan be averted.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":748986,"text":"Can we avert it?"},{"time":751842,"text":"There are companies working\non novel antibiotics,"},{"time":755510,"text":"things the superbugs\nhave never seen before."},{"time":759086,"text":"We need those new drugs badly,"},{"time":761803,"text":"and we need incentives:"},{"time":764055,"text":"discovery grants, extended patents,"},{"time":766586,"text":"prizes, to lure other companies\ninto making antibiotics again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773343,"text":"But that probably won't be enough."},{"time":776059,"text":"Here's why: Evolution always wins."},{"time":780703,"text":"Bacteria birth a new generation\nevery 20 minutes."},{"time":784627,"text":"It takes pharmaceutical chemistry\n10 years to derive a new drug."},{"time":789410,"text":"Every time we use an antibiotic,"},{"time":792266,"text":"we give the bacteria billions of chances"},{"time":795540,"text":"to crack the codes"},{"time":797281,"text":"of the defenses we've constructed."},{"time":800486,"text":"There has never yet been a drug"},{"time":802877,"text":"they could not defeat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805431,"text":"This is asymmetric warfare,"},{"time":808961,"text":"but we can change the outcome."},{"time":813929,"text":"We could build systems to harvest data\nto tell us automatically and specifically"},{"time":820334,"text":"how antibiotics are being used."},{"time":823263,"text":"We could build gatekeeping\ninto drug order systems"},{"time":826096,"text":"so that every prescription\ngets a second look."},{"time":829811,"text":"We could require agriculture\nto give up antibiotic use."},{"time":836243,"text":"We could build surveillance systems"},{"time":839275,"text":"to tell us where resistance\nis emerging next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843501,"text":"Those are the tech solutions."},{"time":846264,"text":"They probably aren't enough either,"},{"time":848888,"text":"unless we help."},{"time":855785,"text":"Antibiotic resistance is a habit."},{"time":858479,"text":"We all know how hard it is\nto change a habit."},{"time":861567,"text":"But as a society,\nwe've done that in the past."},{"time":866397,"text":"People used to toss litter\ninto the streets,"},{"time":869972,"text":"used to not wear seatbelts,"},{"time":871737,"text":"used to smoke inside public buildings."},{"time":876404,"text":"We don't do those things anymore."},{"time":879144,"text":"We don't trash the environment"},{"time":881466,"text":"or court devastating accidents"},{"time":884623,"text":"or expose others\nto the possibility of cancer,"},{"time":887595,"text":"because we decided those things\nwere expensive,"},{"time":891102,"text":"destructive, not in our best interest."},{"time":895815,"text":"We changed social norms."},{"time":899135,"text":"We could change social norms\naround antibiotic use too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905499,"text":"I know that the scale\nof antibiotic resistance"},{"time":907774,"text":"seems overwhelming,"},{"time":909678,"text":"but if you've ever bought\na fluorescent lightbulb"},{"time":913138,"text":"because you were concerned\nabout climate change,"},{"time":915854,"text":"or read the label on a box of crackers"},{"time":918989,"text":"because you think about\nthe deforestation from palm oil,"},{"time":923470,"text":"you already know what it feels like"},{"time":926349,"text":"to take a tiny step to address\nan overwhelming problem."},{"time":931829,"text":"We could take those kinds of steps\nfor antibiotic use too."},{"time":936310,"text":"We could forgo giving an antibiotic\nif we're not sure it's the right one."},{"time":944251,"text":"We could stop insisting on a prescription\nfor our kid's ear infection"},{"time":950564,"text":"before we're sure what caused it."},{"time":953678,"text":"We could ask every restaurant,"},{"time":957045,"text":"every supermarket,"},{"time":958856,"text":"where their meat comes from."},{"time":960806,"text":"We could promise each other"},{"time":962640,"text":"never again to buy chicken\nor shrimp or fruit"},{"time":966745,"text":"raised with routine antibiotic use,"},{"time":969629,"text":"and if we did those things,"},{"time":972323,"text":"we could slow down the arrival\nof the post-antibiotic world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977547,"text":"But we have to do it soon."},{"time":981680,"text":"Penicillin began\nthe antibiotic era in 1943."},{"time":986185,"text":"In just 70 years, we walked ourselves\nup to the edge of disaster."},{"time":992291,"text":"We won't get 70 years"},{"time":994613,"text":"to find our way back out again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998769,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1000789,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}